            <h1>Getting <span class="accent">Started</span></h1>
            <p>This guide will walk you through downloading, installing, and activating GemCrest on your Windows
                computer.</p>

            <h2>System Requirements</h2>
            <p>Before installation, ensure your computer meets these requirements:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Operating System:</strong> Windows 10 or later (64-bit)</li>
                <li><strong>Processor:</strong> Intel Core i3 or equivalent</li>
                <li><strong>RAM:</strong> 4 GB minimum (8 GB recommended)</li>
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> 500 MB available space</li>
                <li><strong>Display:</strong> 1366×768 resolution or higher</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Step 1: Download GemCrest</h2>
            <p>After purchasing a license, you will receive an email containing:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Your unique license code</li>
                <li>Download link for the GemCrest installer</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Step 2: Install the Software</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Double-click the downloaded <code>GemCrest-Setup.exe</code> file</li>
                <li>If Windows Defender prompts you, click "More info" → "Run anyway"</li>
                <li>Follow the installation wizard steps</li>
                <li>Choose your installation location (default is recommended)</li>
                <li>Wait for installation to complete</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Step 3: Activate Your License</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Launch GemCrest from the Start menu or desktop shortcut</li>
                <li>On first launch, you'll see the activation screen</li>
                <li>Enter your license code (format: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX)</li>
                <li>Click "Activate License"</li>
                <li>Your license will be verified and GemCrest will unlock</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="callout callout-info">
                <strong>Note:</strong> License activation requires a one-time internet connection. After activation,
                GemCrest works completely offline.
            </div>

            <h2>Step 4: Set Up Your Shop Profile</h2>
            <p>After activation, configure your shop details:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Shop Profile</strong></li>
                <li>Enter your shop name, address, and contact details</li>
                <li>Add your GST number and PAN</li>
                <li>Upload your shop logo (optional)</li>
                <li>Save your settings</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Step 5: Configure Metal Rates</h2>
            <p>Set up your gold and silver rates:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to <strong>Metal Rates</strong> in the sidebar</li>
                <li>Enter today's rates for 24K gold and fine silver</li>
                <li>The system will auto-calculate rates for other purities</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>You're Ready!</h2>
            <p>GemCrest is now set up and ready to use. Continue to the <a href="<%= path %>docs/user-guide<%= ext %>"
                    style="color:var(--rose-gold);">User Guide</a> to learn how to create your first invoice.</p>
        </main>
